01:19:32,752 --> 01:19:34,460
- They accepted?
- In principle.

1154
01:19:34,627 --> 01:19:37,460
Don Jeffries wants us on the phone in half an hour.

1155
01:19:37,627 --> 01:19:40,544
I tried to explain about Arthur,
but they're short on sympathy.

1156
01:19:40,710 --> 01:19:42,585
Wait a minute. U/North is settling?

1157
01:19:42,752 --> 01:19:46,835
They see a window. They wanna try.
It's their show. What are we gonna do?

1158
01:19:48,585 --> 01:19:51,710
You did what you could, Michael.
We all did.

1159
01:19:53,085 --> 01:19:54,419
It's....

1160
01:19:54,585 --> 01:19:56,252
It's what we got.

1161
01:19:57,419 --> 01:20:00,252
- You need a ride?
- No, thanks, I'm fine.

1162
01:20:33,002 --> 01:20:34,002
Hello.

1163
01:20:34,169 --> 01:20:36,752
Hello. Hi. I'm looking for Anna Kysersun.

1164
01:20:36,960 --> 01:20:38,044
<i>Who is this?</i>

1165
01:20:38,210 --> 01:20:41,710
Michael Clayton. I'm an attorney in
New York. I got your number from Arthur.

1166
01:20:41,877 --> 01:20:44,752
<i>- You have got some nerve.
- Excuse me?</i>

1167
01:20:44,919 --> 01:20:48,710
You get her all the way to New York City
and then leave her at the airport?

1168
01:20:49,127 --> 01:20:50,710
<i>This is not a complicated person.</i>

1169
01:20:50,877 --> 01:20:53,710
<i>This is a girl who's never been farther than Milwaukee.</i>

1170
01:20:53,877 --> 01:20:55,877
<i>- Wait a minute. Now, wait.
- No, you wait.</i>

1171
01:20:56,044 --> 01:21:00,252
She's coming home tomorrow
and when she does, if you call here again--

1172
01:21:00,460 --> 01:21:02,752
Are you telling me she's in New York right now?

1173
01:21:03,210 --> 01:21:05,210
<i>This is a young girl, do you hear me?</i>

1174
01:21:05,377 --> 01:21:07,794
She's in the city right now?

1175
01:21:07,960 --> 01:21:09,544
<i>What kind of people are you?</i>

1176
01:21:09,710 --> 01:21:12,710
Listen. You just stay on the phone
one second. One second.

1177
01:21:45,419 --> 01:21:46,627
<i>Anna.</i>

1178
01:21:49,044 --> 01:21:50,544
Anna?

1179
01:21:51,335 --> 01:21:54,294
My name's Michael Clayton.
I'm a friend of Arthur's.

1180
01:21:54,460 --> 01:21:57,127
I spoke with your sister.
She told me you were here.

1181
01:21:58,460 --> 01:22:00,294
Please open the door, Anna.

1182
01:22:11,627 --> 01:22:13,294
What are you thinking?

1183
01:22:14,127 --> 01:22:19,419
I don't know. I'll watch the door.
You check his car. Let's get some details.

1184
01:22:22,252 --> 01:22:25,502
He didn't want to say exactly what it was.

1185
01:22:27,377 --> 01:22:31,210
Just that when I got here, he would pick me up...

1186
01:22:31,377 --> 01:22:33,752
...and show me, and I would see...

1187
01:22:34,710 --> 01:22:37,585
...that it was something
that would win the whole case.

1188
01:22:40,794 --> 01:22:42,627
Even this morning...

1189
01:22:42,794 --> 01:22:44,419
...I mean, I thought:

1190
01:22:45,960 --> 01:22:50,585
"Okay, if I get to the airport
and the ticket's not there, then I'll know.

1191
01:22:50,794 --> 01:22:55,877
Okay, you're stupid,
and you can go home now."

1192
01:22:58,460 --> 01:23:03,294
But it was there and he paid, like, 800 dollars...

1193
01:23:03,460 --> 01:23:06,127
...for a first-class ticket.

1194
01:23:06,294 --> 01:23:07,794
And I just....

1195
01:23:11,710 --> 01:23:13,627
I got on the plane.

1196
01:23:16,419 --> 01:23:18,335
I believed him.

1197
01:23:23,127 --> 01:23:27,794
You think maybe he was in some way disappointed?

1198
01:23:28,627 --> 01:23:32,585
Let's say that he knew that you
told somebody else about all of this...

1199
01:23:32,794 --> 01:23:36,210
...and, I don't know, in some crazy way,
he was disappointed by that?

1200
01:23:37,335 --> 01:23:40,210
- But I didn't.
- You must have told somebody else.

1201
01:23:40,377 --> 01:23:41,919
No.

1202
01:23:43,127 --> 01:23:45,294
He made me promise.

1203
01:23:46,794 --> 01:23:51,127
You didn't tell anybody else about this?
Not one other person?

1204
01:23:52,294 --> 01:23:53,669
No.

1205
01:23:58,460 --> 01:24:01,377
He really was crazy, wasn't he?

1206
01:24:14,127 --> 01:24:16,960
- You talking about this?
- Let me see.

1207
01:24:18,502 --> 01:24:20,127
- You know what that is?
- Yeah.

1208
01:24:21,085 --> 01:24:24,127
You said a favor.
That's more than a favor.

1209
01:24:24,335 --> 01:24:26,460
Well, nobody's gonna know where it came from.

1210
01:24:27,835 --> 01:24:30,294
- Are you that jammed up?
- What are you talking about?

1211
01:24:30,460 --> 01:24:33,085
Who asked for this?
It's the restaurant, right?

1212
01:24:33,252 --> 01:24:35,752
One of these guys you owe?
"Get me a seal."

1213
01:24:35,919 --> 01:24:37,544
You really wanna know?

1214
01:25:54,794 --> 01:25:57,002
This just gets better and better.

1215
01:25:58,669 --> 01:26:00,252
What are we doing?

1216
01:28:01,794 --> 01:28:02,835
Freeze!

1217
01:28:03,002 --> 01:28:05,710
Right there, asshole! Don't move!

1218
01:28:05,877 --> 01:28:08,169
- It's all right, I'm a friend!
- Get your hands up!

1219
01:28:08,335 --> 01:28:10,835
Get your hands up now! Now!

1220
01:28:11,044 --> 01:28:12,960
- What's in your hand?
- It's a book.

1221
01:28:13,127 --> 01:28:16,002
Drop it! Drop it, now! Drop it!

1222
01:28:16,169 --> 01:28:19,460
- Turn around. Slowly.
- All right. All right. Okay.

1223
01:28:19,627 --> 01:28:21,460
- Who else is here?
- Nobody.

1224
01:28:21,627 --> 01:28:24,044
- I said, who else is here?
- Nobody's here!

1225
01:28:24,210 --> 01:28:25,627
Check in there.

1226
01:28:26,419 --> 01:28:29,710
You move, I'll take your head off.

1227
01:28:59,544 --> 01:29:04,002
Now I owe this scumbag and his wife--
Who's a complete piece of shit in my unit.

1228
01:29:04,169 --> 01:29:06,252
- Now I owe them both my balls.
- I'm sorry.

1229
01:29:06,419 --> 01:29:08,419
- You know I am.
- "Nobody will know it's me."

1230
01:29:08,585 --> 01:29:11,669
You know what happens they don't
bury this, that I gave you this?

1231
01:29:11,835 --> 01:29:13,210
It's bad. I know it.

1232
01:29:13,377 --> 01:29:16,419
I'm 18 months away from my 20.
You just put my pension in jeopardy.

1233
01:29:16,585 --> 01:29:18,544
- You made your point.
- It's not a point!

1234
01:29:18,710 --> 01:29:21,085
- Who called 911?
- What?

1235
01:29:21,377 --> 01:29:24,335
The building was empty. I was quiet.
I wasn't there very long.

1236
01:29:24,502 --> 01:29:26,919
Who called it in?
Does that make sense to you--?

1237
01:29:27,085 --> 01:29:28,669
This never happened.

1238
01:29:29,960 --> 01:29:32,002
You got these cops thinking you're a lawyer.

1239
01:29:32,169 --> 01:29:34,210
You got these lawyers thinking you're a cop.

1240
01:29:34,377 --> 01:29:38,502
You got everybody fooled, don't you?
Everybody but you.

1241
01:29:38,710 --> 01:29:40,794
You know exactly what you are.

1242
01:29:54,377 --> 01:29:55,919
We tried calling you six times.

1243
01:29:56,085 --> 01:29:58,210
But your machine must be busted or something.

1244
01:30:00,085 --> 01:30:01,544
We gave it our best shot.

1245
01:30:02,919 --> 01:30:05,377
We ran out of red covers.
We only had 2000 in stock...

1246
01:30:05,585 --> 01:30:07,419
...so we did the other thousand in blue.

1247
01:30:28,835 --> 01:30:30,335
Is everything all right?

1248
01:30:30,502 --> 01:30:31,710
It's fine, yeah.

1249
01:30:32,419 --> 01:30:35,502
You have a van or something?
Because I have 25 boxes back there--

1250
01:30:35,669 --> 01:30:38,710
Do me a favor. Hang on to them.

1251
01:30:38,919 --> 01:30:41,127
I'll come back and pick everything up next week.

1252
01:30:41,294 --> 01:30:43,377
- Seriously? Thanks, man.
- Yeah.

1253
01:31:03,919 --> 01:31:05,252
Hello.

1254
01:31:10,335 --> 01:31:13,627
Don. You go ahead. I'll catch up to you.

1255
01:31:14,210 --> 01:31:15,502
What?

1256
01:31:22,919 --> 01:31:25,044
<i>Do you know Michael Clayton?</i>

1257
01:31:25,252 --> 01:31:26,710
<i>Yeah, why?</i>

1258
01:31:26,919 --> 01:31:28,669
We have a situation.

1259
01:31:48,419 --> 01:31:50,002
Hey, did they find you?

1260
01:31:50,169 --> 01:31:53,210
- Who?
- Marty. I don't think they've gone in yet.

1261
01:32:01,377 --> 01:32:02,710
Marty.

1262
01:32:03,044 --> 01:32:06,210
Your phone's off. There's too much
going on for your phone to be off.

1263
01:32:06,419 --> 01:32:08,377
- I need a minute.
- Yeah, well, we're late--

1264
01:32:08,585 --> 01:32:10,210
We never got to finish last night.

1265
01:32:10,377 --> 01:32:12,502
Did you close the place?
You look like hell.

1266
01:32:12,669 --> 01:32:15,710
- No, I left right after you left.
- If you say so.

1267
01:32:15,919 --> 01:32:18,585
We've been here all night.
We had to make an announcement.

1268
01:32:18,752 --> 01:32:22,044
Jean! I need the thing, the envelope.

1269
01:32:22,210 --> 01:32:25,419
I wanted your input. I couldn't get you.
I had to pull the trigger.

1270
01:32:25,585 --> 01:32:28,502
I put Bob Nast and Kim, probably a mistake.

1271
01:32:28,669 --> 01:32:32,002
They're gonna pull together a memorial
service by the end of the week.

1272
01:32:32,169 --> 01:32:34,419
I told them to call you if they need any help.

1273
01:32:34,919 --> 01:32:37,710
No, no, no.
The other one. The other one.

1274
01:32:38,252 --> 01:32:40,585
So we cut you a check this morning.

1275
01:32:40,752 --> 01:32:44,044
There's some strings attached.
And Barry....

1276
01:32:44,210 --> 01:32:48,335
There's no way around this,
Barry's gonna have to be involved.

1277
01:32:52,085 --> 01:32:54,544
What if Arthur was on to something?

1278
01:32:54,710 --> 01:32:56,377
What do you mean? On to what?

1279
01:32:56,544 --> 01:32:59,419
U/North. What if he wasn't crazy?
What if he was right?

1280
01:32:59,585 --> 01:33:01,752
Right about what?
That we're on the wrong side?

1281
01:33:01,919 --> 01:33:04,335
Wrong side, wrong way, everything, all of it.

1282
01:33:04,502 --> 01:33:07,419
This is news?
This case reeked from day one.

1283
01:33:07,627 --> 01:33:09,585
I gotta tell you how we pay the rent?

1284
01:33:09,752 --> 01:33:12,502
What would they do?
What would they do if he went public?

1285
01:33:12,669 --> 01:33:16,085
What would they do? Are you fucking soft?
They're doing it.

1286
01:33:16,252 --> 01:33:18,669
We don't straighten the settlement out in 24 hours...

1287
01:33:18,835 --> 01:33:20,877
...they're gonna withhold
$9 million in fees.

1288
01:33:21,085 --> 01:33:24,044
Then they'll pull out the video of
Arthur doing his flashdance.

1289
01:33:24,210 --> 01:33:25,919
They'll sue us for legal malpractice.

1290
01:33:26,127 --> 01:33:29,752
Except there won't be anything to win
because the London merger will be dead...

1291
01:33:29,960 --> 01:33:32,585
...and we'll be selling off
the goddamn furniture.

1292
01:33:33,085 --> 01:33:34,752
That's 80.

1293
01:33:35,294 --> 01:33:37,085
We're calling it a bonus.

1294
01:33:37,919 --> 01:33:39,919
Three-year contract
at your current numbers.

1295
01:33:40,127 --> 01:33:41,752
That's assuming this all works out.

1296
01:33:41,919 --> 01:33:43,085
You're doing this now?

1297
01:33:44,752 --> 01:33:48,085
Look, I agreed to this, okay?
But there's rules now.

1298
01:33:48,252 --> 01:33:51,127
You want the contract,
you sign a confidentiality agreement.

1299
01:33:51,294 --> 01:33:53,377
It's gonna be bulletproof and retroactive.

1300
01:33:53,544 --> 01:33:55,252
Because Marty's too nice to say it...

1301
01:33:55,460 --> 01:33:59,252
...but with all you know about this place,
the clients and people who work here...

1302
01:33:59,419 --> 01:34:01,960
...it makes it a little weird
when you ask for 80 grand.

1303
01:34:02,627 --> 01:34:05,335
If I was gonna shake anybody down, I'd come to you...

1304
01:34:05,502 --> 01:34:08,169
...and it wouldn't be for 80 grand.
Is this him or you?

1305
01:34:08,335 --> 01:34:10,919
- If I'm wrong, I apologize.
- You're way the fuck wrong.

1306
01:34:11,127 --> 01:34:12,335
So there you go.

1307
01:34:12,502 --> 01:34:14,169
Enough. Okay? Everybody.

1308
01:34:15,044 --> 01:34:17,210
He's an asshole, but he knows it.

1309
01:34:17,627 --> 01:34:20,877
And you're on the record.
Okay? Everybody happy?

1310
01:34:21,502 --> 01:34:24,210
- Don Jeffries is here.
- We're on the way.

1311
01:34:25,002 --> 01:34:29,085
Call Bob Nast.
Just see if they need help with this thing.

1312
01:34:32,669 --> 01:34:34,044
You're welcome.

1313
01:35:26,877 --> 01:35:29,252
You said 12. This is 75.

1314
01:35:29,419 --> 01:35:31,585
Well, don't get too excited.
You want a drink?

1315
01:35:31,752 --> 01:35:33,627
No. I'm working.

1316
01:35:36,044 --> 01:35:39,585
So we're square, then. No bad blood.

1317
01:35:39,752 --> 01:35:41,460
You're just doing your job.

1318
01:35:41,627 --> 01:35:43,085
That's right.

1319
01:35:44,002 --> 01:35:45,752
Take it easy, Gabe.

1320
01:35:46,752 --> 01:35:48,127
Michael.

1321
01:35:59,835 --> 01:36:01,294
<i>Check.</i>

1322
01:36:03,127 --> 01:36:04,377
<i>Check.</i>

1323
01:36:04,710 --> 01:36:07,460
- Check.
- Half the pot. Two hundred.

1324
01:36:07,627 --> 01:36:08,919
Two hundred to go.

1325
01:36:46,252 --> 01:36:48,002
So, what happened with the bar?

1326
01:36:48,169 --> 01:36:50,210
You just had to be a rock star, huh?

1327
01:37:12,669 --> 01:37:15,460
What are you doing? You just got here.

1328
01:37:15,627 --> 01:37:17,544
Guy plays nine hands, walks away.

1329
01:37:17,710 --> 01:37:21,877
I scare you away? What did I do?
Did I scare you away?

1330
01:37:57,627 --> 01:37:58,669
Get out.

1331
01:38:00,044 --> 01:38:02,169
<i>Get out of the car now.</i>

1332
01:38:03,919 --> 01:38:04,919
<i>- Walter?
- Michael.</i>

1333
01:38:05,085 --> 01:38:07,294
<i>- Michael. Thank God you're there.
- Yeah.</i>

1334
01:38:11,669 --> 01:38:13,627
You have eight...

1335
01:38:14,502 --> 01:38:17,252
<i>...six, five...</i>

1336
01:38:17,419 --> 01:38:19,752
<i>...four, three....</i>

1337
01:38:19,919 --> 01:38:21,544
<i>Get out of the car.</i>

1338
01:38:25,002 --> 01:38:28,002
<i>- Tell him to stay off the phone.
- All right. But you're on it?</i>

1339
01:38:28,627 --> 01:38:30,044
Am I clean?

1340
01:38:30,210 --> 01:38:31,460
Just keep walking.

1341
01:38:31,627 --> 01:38:33,835
You copy. Am I clean?

1342
01:38:34,044 --> 01:38:37,044
Just keep moving.
He's walking to the car.

1343
01:38:37,585 --> 01:38:41,127
<i>- -to let him know you're on the way.
I'll get back to you with the details.</i>

1344
01:38:41,335 --> 01:38:43,752
<i>- Just give me two minutes.
- I'll be in the car.</i>

1345
01:38:47,460 --> 01:38:50,877
<i>I didn't finish. It's in, but I don't know.</i>

1346
01:39:19,044 --> 01:39:22,585
It's loose. I got a pulse.
He's up there somewhere, but....

1347
01:39:24,377 --> 01:39:26,294
Let's find a way to boost the signal.

1348
01:39:33,877 --> 01:39:37,044
- I don't know what Walter promised you--
- A miracle worker!

1349
01:39:37,210 --> 01:39:40,460
That's Walter on the phone,
20 minutes ago. Direct quote, okay?

1350
01:39:40,627 --> 01:39:42,460
"I'm sending you a miracle worker."

1351
01:39:42,627 --> 01:39:44,294
- Well, he misspoke.
- About what?

1352
01:39:44,460 --> 01:39:47,960
About the fact that you're the firm's fixer?
Or that you're any good at it?

1353
01:39:53,752 --> 01:39:55,710
We're up. Just got a signal.

1354
01:40:19,544 --> 01:40:21,877
There's nothing back this way.
What's he doing?

1355
01:40:22,044 --> 01:40:23,252
Maybe he's lost.

1356
01:40:23,419 --> 01:40:25,210
- Wait a minute.
- That's him.

1357
01:40:28,544 --> 01:40:29,794
He was alone, right?

1358
01:40:29,960 --> 01:40:32,752
- Yeah, I think so.
- Call it, yes or no?

1359
01:40:35,210 --> 01:40:36,835
We gotta turn around.

1360
01:41:07,044 --> 01:41:08,669
Talk to me.

1361
01:41:08,835 --> 01:41:10,377
It's strobing.

1362
01:41:10,544 --> 01:41:12,960
No, we're good. I think we're good.
Just keep going.

1363
01:41:28,752 --> 01:41:30,335
No, he turned. Somehow he turned.

1364
01:41:30,544 --> 01:41:31,877
- Where?
- He took--

1365
01:41:32,377 --> 01:41:34,377
- He took a left.
- I don't have a left.

1366
01:41:44,335 --> 01:41:47,252
- East. He's southeast.
- What, so we missed it?

1367
01:41:47,419 --> 01:41:49,544
- Or the grid is wrong.
- Hang on.

1368
01:41:59,710 --> 01:42:02,419
- We gotta go back to one.
- One is what? Where's our one?

1369
01:42:02,627 --> 01:42:05,627
Half a mile straight ahead.
Just keep driving. Just go.

1370
01:42:12,502 --> 01:42:15,127
It says we're closing.
But that's west. It can't be west.

1371
01:42:15,294 --> 01:42:16,335
The signal or the grid?

1372
01:42:16,544 --> 01:42:19,252
- It's both. It just keeps dropping out.
- Goddamn it.

1373
01:43:10,419 --> 01:43:11,919
Give me the cell.

1374
01:43:14,419 --> 01:43:16,127
Our signal's good.

1375
01:44:53,919 --> 01:44:55,210
What?

1376
01:44:57,835 --> 01:44:59,544
Thanks, Mickey.

1377
01:44:59,710 --> 01:45:01,377
Just get me out of here.

1378
01:45:09,085 --> 01:45:12,794
I wanna get a meeting scheduled on this,
soon as we can. Thursday at the latest.

1379
01:45:12,960 --> 01:45:16,585
I think we should have someone from
the equity group there. Maybe McDonnell--

1380
01:45:16,752 --> 01:45:18,252
- Yeah?
- Did you hear?

1381
01:45:18,419 --> 01:45:20,960
- Yeah, yeah. They closed U/North.
- No. Michael Clayton.

1382
01:45:21,419 --> 01:45:22,460
What?

1383
01:45:22,627 --> 01:45:25,544
Car bomb. Upstate. This morning.
He was killed.

1384
01:45:26,585 --> 01:45:27,585
What?

1385
01:45:29,294 --> 01:45:31,085
Holy shit.

1386
01:45:45,294 --> 01:45:50,210
<i>It has been and it remains the U/North position...</i>

1387
01:45:50,377 --> 01:45:54,460
<i>...that this lawsuit is baseless
and without merit.</i>

1388
01:45:54,627 --> 01:45:58,710
Our reluctance to negotiate was anchored by this belief...

1389
01:45:58,877 --> 01:46:04,044
...and reinforced by the plaintiffs' demand
for settlement...

1390
01:46:04,210 --> 01:46:06,752
...in excess of 3 billion dollars.

1391
01:46:06,960 --> 01:46:10,377
The reason that we are all here today is...

1392
01:46:10,585 --> 01:46:14,419
...that several key elements
in the case have changed.

1393
01:46:15,460 --> 01:46:19,877
<i>You all have a tentative proposal packet...</i>

1394
01:46:20,460 --> 01:46:24,419
<i>...which outlines the details,
but the bottom line is this:</i>

1395
01:46:24,627 --> 01:46:27,377
<i>Over the past several months we had gotten word...</i>

1396
01:46:27,544 --> 01:46:30,877
...that the plaintiffs were
growing impatient...

1397
01:46:31,044 --> 01:46:34,877
...and were in the process
of revising their settlement numbers.

1398
01:46:35,377 --> 01:46:36,835
<i>We also learned...</i>

1399
01:46:37,002 --> 01:46:40,960
<i>...that the plaintiffs' attorneys' fees
were capped at 32 percent...</i>

1400
01:46:41,127 --> 01:46:43,210
<i>...up to 400 million dollars...</i>

1401
01:46:43,627 --> 01:46:47,877
...above which,
their fees dropped to 24 percent.

1402
01:46:48,044 --> 01:46:52,585
So we knew that there would be
this motivational dead zone for them...

1403
01:46:52,794 --> 01:46:54,127
...in the middle there.

1404
01:46:54,877 --> 01:46:56,585
<i>Finally...</i>

1405
01:46:56,752 --> 01:47:01,085
...our finance team informed us
that they had run the numbers...

1406
01:47:01,252 --> 01:47:03,085
...and that the tax benefit...

1407
01:47:03,252 --> 01:47:06,460
...provided that we bring
the settlement in under 600 million...

1408
01:47:06,627 --> 01:47:09,085
...and within this fiscal year...

1409
01:47:09,252 --> 01:47:15,127
...that the write-off on this settlement
would essentially pay for itself.

1410
01:47:15,627 --> 01:47:19,794
<i>The package that you have before you
represents, in my judgment...</i>

1411
01:47:20,252 --> 01:47:25,044
<i>...the strongest possible position for
our company under the circumstances.</i>

1412
01:47:25,210 --> 01:47:26,919
<i>And, as chief counsel...</i>

1413
01:47:27,085 --> 01:47:30,335
...it is my recommendation
that this proposal be confirmed.

1414
01:47:31,419 --> 01:47:34,919
Thank you, Karen. If you just give us
a few minutes to talk about it.

1415
01:47:35,127 --> 01:47:37,377
Certainly. I'll be right outside.

1416
01:47:39,794 --> 01:47:40,752
Well....

1417
01:48:03,877 --> 01:48:05,710
How'd it go in there?

1418
01:48:08,752 --> 01:48:10,960
Pretty freaky, huh?

1419
01:48:11,127 --> 01:48:14,085
Did you see Arthur?
He's wandering around here somewhere.

1420
01:48:16,627 --> 01:48:19,877
I'm kidding. Lighten up.

1421
01:48:21,460 --> 01:48:25,127
You got one of these? It's a great memo.
It's an oldie but a goodie.

1422
01:48:28,294 --> 01:48:29,794
Got your heart racing, don't I?

1423
01:48:29,960 --> 01:48:32,085
I don't know what it is you think you're doing.

1424
01:48:32,252 --> 01:48:33,627
What do you think I'm doing?

1425
01:48:33,794 --> 01:48:35,585
The suit's over. We have a deal.

1426
01:48:35,752 --> 01:48:38,460
Whatever that is, it's meaningless at this point.

1427
01:48:38,627 --> 01:48:42,294
You think? I must have gotten it wrong.
I thought you had a tentative proposal.

1428
01:48:42,460 --> 01:48:44,627
I didn't realize you'd signed all those checks.

1429
01:48:44,835 --> 01:48:48,127
That's a drag. I got a thousand of these.
What am I gonna do with them?

1430
01:48:48,294 --> 01:48:49,627
I'm calling Marty.

1431
01:48:49,794 --> 01:48:52,127
Good. Good. Do it.
That's a great place to start.

1432
01:48:52,335 --> 01:48:55,127
Let's find out who told him
Arthur was calling Anna Kysersun.

1433
01:48:55,294 --> 01:48:57,127
Let's find out who tapped those phones.

1434
01:48:57,294 --> 01:49:01,085
This memorandum, even if it's authentic,
which I doubt, I highly doubt--

1435
01:49:01,252 --> 01:49:04,669
- I know what you did to Arthur.
- It's protected. It belongs to U/North.

1436
01:49:04,835 --> 01:49:07,627
- I know you killed him.
- It's attorney-client privilege.

1437
01:49:07,794 --> 01:49:11,460
See, now, that's just not the way to go here, Karen.

1438
01:49:11,627 --> 01:49:14,294
For such a smart person, you really are lost, aren't you?

1439
01:49:14,502 --> 01:49:15,794
This conversation is over.

1440
01:49:16,002 --> 01:49:19,419
I'm not the guy that you kill.
I'm the guy that you buy.

1441
01:49:19,585 --> 01:49:22,127
Are you so fucking blind you don't even see what I am?

1442
01:49:22,294 --> 01:49:25,752
I'm the easiest part of your whole
goddamn problem and you're gonna kill me?

1443
01:49:26,085 --> 01:49:29,210
Don't you know who I am?
I'm a fixer. I'm a bagman.

1444
01:49:29,377 --> 01:49:32,794
I do everything from shoplifting housewives
to bent congressmen...

1445
01:49:32,960 --> 01:49:34,835
...and you're gonna kill me?

1446
01:49:35,794 --> 01:49:38,627
What do you need, Karen? Lay it on me.

1447
01:49:38,794 --> 01:49:42,460
You want a carry permit? You want
a heads-up on an insider-trading subpoena?

1448
01:49:42,669 --> 01:49:46,502
I sold out Arthur for 80 grand
and a contract and you're gonna kill me?

1449
01:49:48,002 --> 01:49:49,419
What do you want?

1450
01:49:49,585 --> 01:49:51,127
What do I want?

1451
01:49:51,294 --> 01:49:52,877
I want more.

1452
01:49:53,377 --> 01:49:55,127
I want out.

1453
01:49:55,335 --> 01:49:57,960
And with this, I want everything.

1454
01:49:59,710 --> 01:50:00,960
Is there a number?

1455
01:50:01,127 --> 01:50:02,710
Ten is a number.

1456
01:50:02,877 --> 01:50:04,919
Ten? Ten what?

1457
01:50:06,960 --> 01:50:08,460
Ten million?

1458
01:50:08,627 --> 01:50:12,044
Where do you think I'm gonna get 10 million dollars?

1459
01:50:12,627 --> 01:50:14,502
You know what's great about this?

1460
01:50:14,669 --> 01:50:17,002
Did you read it to the end?
You see who signed it?

1461
01:50:17,544 --> 01:50:19,460
Let's go in and ask Don Jeffries...

1462
01:50:19,627 --> 01:50:22,627
...if he wants to pass the hat
for a worthy cause.

1463
01:50:24,460 --> 01:50:26,835
This would have to be a longer conversation...

1464
01:50:27,002 --> 01:50:29,127
...and would have to take place
somewhere else.

1465
01:50:29,335 --> 01:50:30,794
Where? My car?

1466
01:50:32,377 --> 01:50:33,419
All right.

1467
01:50:34,585 --> 01:50:37,627
I'm gonna make it easy.
Let's make it 5.

1468
01:50:37,794 --> 01:50:39,585
Five and I'll forget about Arthur.

1469
01:50:41,960 --> 01:50:46,710
Five is easier. Yeah, 5 is something
that we could talk about.

1470
01:50:46,877 --> 01:50:50,627
Good. And then the other 5 is
to forget about the 468 people...

1471
01:50:50,794 --> 01:50:52,877
...that you knocked off
with your weed killer.

1472
01:50:53,044 --> 01:50:55,419
Let me finish up this meeting.
I'll talk to Don--

1473
01:50:55,585 --> 01:50:58,169
Do I look like I'm negotiating?!

1474
01:50:58,335 --> 01:50:59,669
Karen?

1475
01:51:00,377 --> 01:51:02,252
- One second.
- Everything okay?

1476
01:51:03,627 --> 01:51:04,627
Yes.

1477
01:51:05,627 --> 01:51:09,419
Ten million dollars. Bank of my choosing.
Offshore. lmmediately.

1478
01:51:09,585 --> 01:51:10,710
- Yes.
- Say it!

1479
01:51:10,877 --> 01:51:14,752
Ten million dollars, your account,
the moment this meeting is through.

1480
01:51:14,919 --> 01:51:17,210
- Karen! Everyone's waiting.
- I'm coming, Don.

1481
01:51:18,252 --> 01:51:19,627
You have a deal.

1482
01:51:20,169 --> 01:51:21,460
You're so fucked.

1483
01:51:21,794 --> 01:51:23,127
What?

1484
01:51:23,627 --> 01:51:25,502
- You're fucked.
- What do you mean?

1485
01:51:25,669 --> 01:51:27,877
- Take a wild guess.
- Is there a problem?

1486
01:51:28,044 --> 01:51:30,752
- I don't understand.
- Let me get a picture while I'm at it.

1487
01:51:30,919 --> 01:51:33,710
- You don't want the money?
- Keep the money. You'll need it.

1488
01:51:33,877 --> 01:51:35,460
Is this fellow bothering you?

1489
01:51:35,669 --> 01:51:36,877
Am I bothering you?

1490
01:51:37,044 --> 01:51:41,085
Karen, I've got a board waiting in there.
What the hell's going on? Who are you?

1491
01:51:41,252 --> 01:51:42,960
I'm Shiva, the god of death.

1492
01:51:43,127 --> 01:51:46,752
Ron! Ronny, I need security
out here immediately.

1493
01:51:47,669 --> 01:51:48,919
All right. Here we go.

1494
01:51:49,085 --> 01:51:52,294
That guy right there, stop him.
Grab that guy.

1495
01:51:53,877 --> 01:51:56,627
- What are you doing?
- We're detectives with the N.Y.P.D.

1496
01:51:56,794 --> 01:51:59,127
Come back with us and we'll explain everything.

1497
01:51:59,294 --> 01:52:02,544
Check on her. Make sure she doesn't need
any medical attention.

1498
01:52:02,710 --> 01:52:04,877
You guys go into the ballroom.
Nobody leaves.

1499
01:52:05,044 --> 01:52:06,835
Have your guys cover every exit.

1500
01:52:07,002 --> 01:52:09,794
Will you please explain to me what's going on here?

1501
01:52:10,419 --> 01:52:11,794
Did you get all that?

1502
01:52:11,960 --> 01:52:14,169
Yeah. Got it.

1503
01:52:17,794 --> 01:52:20,627
- You okay?
- Yeah. Just gotta get some air.

1504
01:52:20,794 --> 01:52:22,294
Sure.

1505
01:52:22,669 --> 01:52:25,419
Just stay close, okay?

1506
01:52:25,585 --> 01:52:26,835
Okay.

1507
01:53:37,377 --> 01:53:39,210
So, what are we doing?

1508
01:53:46,294 --> 01:53:48,294
Give me 50 dollars' worth.

1509
01:53:50,169 --> 01:53:51,835
Just drive.

